obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9565)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9565&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Gram Nyayalayas Act,`
  line 2008.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^1***, the State of Nagaland, the State of Arunachal Pradesh, the`
  line `State of Sikkim and to the tribal areas.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this sub-section, the expression tribal areas means the areas specified in Parts I,`
  line `II, IIA and III of the Table below paragraph 20 of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution within the State`
  line `of Assam, the State of Meghalaya, the State of Tripura and the State of Mizoram, respectively.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different States.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 2nd October, 2009, vide notification No. S.O. 2313(E), dated 11th November, 2009, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9566)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9566&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Gram Nyayalaya" means a court established under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Gram Panchayat" means an institution (by whatever name called) of self-government`
  line `constituted, at the village level, under article 243B of the Constitution, for the rural areas;`
  line
  line `(c) "High Court" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any State, the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Union territory to which the jurisdiction of the High Court for a State has`
  line `been extended by law, that High Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to any other Union territory, the highest Court of criminal appeal for that`
  line `territory other than the Supreme Court of India;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(e) "Nyayadhikari" means the presiding officer of a Gram Nyayalaya appointed under section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) "Panchayat at intermediate level" means an institution (by whatever name called) of selfgovernment constituted, at the intermediate level, under article 243B of the Constitution, for the rural`
  line `areas in accordance with the provisions of Part IX of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof appointed`
  line `under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(j) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908) or the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in those Codes.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9567)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Gram Nyayalayas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9567&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of exercising the jurisdiction and`
  line `powers conferred on a Gram Nyayalaya by this Act, the State Government, after consultation with the`
  line `High Court, may, by notification, establish one or more Gram Nyayalayas for every Panchayat at`
  line `intermediate level or a group of contiguous Panchayats at intermediate level in a district or where there is`
  line `no Panchayat at intermediate level in any State, for a group of contiguous Gram Panchayats.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, after consultation with the High Court, specify, by notification, the`
  line `local limits of the area to which the jurisdiction of a Gram Nyayalaya shall extend and may, at any time,`
  line `increase, reduce or alter such limits.`
  line
  line `(3) The Gram Nyayalayas established under sub-section (1) shall be in addition to the courts`
  line `established under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9568)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Headquarters of Gram Nyayalayas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9568&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The headquarters of every Gram Nyayalaya shall be`
  line `located at the headquarters of the intermediate Panchayat in which the Gram Nyayalaya is established or`
  line `such other place as may be notified by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9569)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Appointment of Nyayadhikari.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9569&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, in consultation with the High`
  line `Court, appoint a Nyayadhikari for every Gram Nyayalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9570)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Nyayadhikari.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9570&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be qualified to be`
  line `appointed as a Nyayadhikari unless he is eligible to be appointed as a Judicial Magistrate of the first class.`
  line
  line `(2) While appointing a Nyayadhikari, representation shall be given to the members of the Scheduled`
  line `Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, women and such other classes or communities as may be specified by`
  line `notification, by the State Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9571)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Nyayadhikari.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9571&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The salary`
  line `and other allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, a Nyayadhikari shall be`
  line `such as may be applicable to the Judicial Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9572)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Nyayadhikari not to preside over proceedings in which he is interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9572&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Nyayadhikari`
  line `shall not preside over the proceedings of a Gram Nyayalaya in which he has any interest or is otherwise`
  line `involved in the subject matter of the dispute or is related to any party to such proceedings and in such a`
  line `case, the Nyayadhikari shall refer the matter to the District Court or the Court of Session, as the case may`
  line `be, for transferring it to any other Nyayadhikari.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9573)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Nyayadhikari to hold mobile courts and conduct proceedings in villages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9573&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Nyayadhikari shall periodically visit the villages falling under his jurisdiction and conduct trial or`
  line `proceedings at any place which he considers is in close proximity to the place where the parties ordinarily`
  line `reside or where the whole or part of the cause of action had arisen:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Gram Nyayalaya decides to hold mobile court outside its headquarters, it`
  line `shall give wide publicity as to the date and place where it proposes to hold mobile court.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall extend all facilities to the Gram Nyayalaya including the provision of`
  line `vehicles for holding mobile court by the Nyayadhikari while conducting trial or proceedings outside its`
  line headquarters.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9574)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Seal of Gram Nyayalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9574&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every Gram Nyayalaya established under this Act shall use a seal of`
  line `the court in such form and dimensions as may be prescribed by the High Court with the approval of the`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9575)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Jurisdiction of Gram Nyayalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9575&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Gram Nyayalaya shall exercise both civil and criminal jurisdiction in the`
  line `manner and to the extent provided under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9576)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Criminal jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9576&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force, the Gram Nyayalaya may take cognizance of an offence on a complaint or on a police report and shall—`
  line
  line `(a) try all offences specified in Part I of the First Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) try all offences and grant relief, if any, specified under the enactments included in Part II of`
  line `that Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Gram Nyayalaya shall also try all such`
  line `offences or grant such relief under the State Acts which may be notified by the State Government under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9577)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Civil jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9577&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908) or any other law for the time being in force, and subject to sub-section (2), the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya shall have jurisdiction to—`
  line
  line `(a) try all suits or proceedings of a civil nature falling under the classes of disputes specified in`
  line `Part I of the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) try all classes of claims and disputes which may be notified by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14 and by the State Government under sub-section (3) of the said section.`
  line
  line `(2) The pecuniary limits of the Gram Nyayalaya shall be such as may be specified by the High Court,`
  line `in consultation with the State Government, by notification, from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9578)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9578&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary`
  line `or expedient so to do, it may, by notification, add to or omit any item in Part I or Part II of the First`
  line `Schedule or Part II of the Second Schedule, as the case may be, and it shall be deemed to have been`
  line `amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(3) If the State Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, in`
  line `consultation with the High Court, by notification, add to any item in Part III of the First Schedule or Part`
  line `III of the Second Schedule or omit from it any item in respect of which the State Legislature is competent`
  line `to make laws and thereupon the First Schedule or the Second Schedule, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification issued under sub-section (3) shall be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9579)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9579&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) shall be applicable to`
  line `the suits triable by the Gram Nyayalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall be`
  line `applicable in respect of the offences triable by the Gram Nyayalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9580)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9580&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Court or the Court of Session, as the case`
  line `may be, with effect from such date as may be notified by the High Court, may transfer all the civil or`
  line `criminal cases, pending before the courts subordinate to it, to the Gram Nyayalaya competent to try or`
  line `dispose of such cases.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Nyayalaya may, in its discretion, either retry the cases or proceed from the stage at`
  line `which it was transferred to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9581)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duties of ministerial officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9581&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall determine the nature and`
  line `categories of the officers and other employees required to assist a Gram Nyayalaya in the discharge of its`
  line `functions and provide the Gram Nyayalaya with such officers and other employees as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other conditions of service of, the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Gram Nyayalaya shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers and other employees of a Gram Nyayalaya shall perform such duties as may, from`
  line `time to time, be assigned to them by the Nyayadhikari.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9582)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Overriding effect of Act in criminal trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9582&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other`
  line `law, but save as expressly provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code shall, in so far as they are not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply to the proceedings before a Gram Nyayalaya; and for`
  line `the purpose of the said provisions of the Code, the Gram Nyayalaya shall be deemed to be a Court of`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9583)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Gram Nyayalaya to follow summary trial procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9583&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (1) of section 260 or sub-section (2) of section 262 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) the Gram Nyayalaya shall try the offences in a summary way in accordance`
  line `with the procedure specified in Chapter XXI of the said Code and the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 262 and sections 263 to 265 of the said Code, shall, so far as may be, apply to such trial.`
  line
  line `(2) When, in the course of a summary trial, it appears to the Nyayadhikari that the nature of the case`
  line `is such that it is undesirable to try it summarily, the Nyayadhikari shall recall any witness who may have`
  line `been examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the manner provided under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9584)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Plea bargaining before Gram Nyayalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9584&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `A person accused of an offence may file an`
  line `application for plea bargaining in Gram Nyayalaya in which such offence is pending trial and the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya shall dispose of the case in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XXIA of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9585)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Conduct of cases in Gram Nyayalaya and legal aid to parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9585&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of`
  line `conducting criminal cases in the Gram Nyayalaya on behalf of the Government, the provisions of section`
  line `25 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), in a criminal proceeding before the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya, the complainant may engage an advocate of his choice at his expense to present the case of`
  line `prosecution with the leave of the Gram Nyayalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Legal Services Authority, constituted under section 6 of the Legal Services Authorities`
  line `Act, 1987 (39 of 1987) shall prepare a panel of advocates and assign at least two of them to be attached to`
  line `each Gram Nyayalaya so that their services may be provided by the Gram Nyayalaya to the accused`
  line `unable to engage an advocate.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9586)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Pronouncement of judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9586&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The judgment in every trial shall be pronounced by the`
  line `Nyayadhikari in open court immediately after the termination of the trial or at any subsequent time, not`
  line `exceeding fifteen days, of which notice shall be given to the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Nyayalaya shall deliver a copy of its judgment immediately to both the parties free of`
  line cost.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9587)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Overriding effect of Act in civil proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9587&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or any other law, but save as expressly provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code shall, in so far as they are not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply to the proceedings before a Gram Nyayalaya; and for`
  line `the purpose of the said provisions of the Code, the Gram Nyayalaya shall be deemed to be a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (9588)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Special procedure in civil disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9588&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, every suit, claim or dispute under this Act shall be instituted by making an`
  line `application to the Gram Nyayalaya in such form, in such manner, and accompanied by such fee, not`
  line `exceeding rupees one hundred, as may be prescribed by the High Court, from time to time, in consultation`
  line `with the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a suit, claim or dispute has been duly instituted, a summons shall be issued by the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya, accompanied by a copy of the application made under sub-section (1), to the opposite party to`
  line `appear and answer the claim by such date as may be specified therein and the same shall be served in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) After the opposite party files his written statement, the Gram Nyayalaya shall fix a date for`
  line `hearing and inform all the parties to be present in person or through their advocates.`
  line
  line `(4) On the date fixed for hearing, the Gram Nyayalaya shall hear both the parties in regard to their`
  line `respective contentions and where the dispute does not require recording of any evidence, pronounce the`
  line `judgment; and in case where it requires recording of evidence, the Gram Nyayalaya shall proceed further.`
  line
  line `(5) The Gram Nyayalaya shall also have the power—`
  line
  line `(a) to dismiss any case for default or to proceed ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(b) to set aside any such order of dismissal for default or any order passed by it for hearing the`
  line `case ex parte.`
  line
  line `(6) In regard to any incidental matter that may arise during the course of the proceedings, the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya shall adopt such procedure as it may deem just and reasonable in the interest of justice.`
  line
  line `(7) The proceedings shall, as far as practicable, be consistent with the interests of justice and the`
  line `hearing shall be continued on a day-to-day basis until its conclusion, unless the Gram Nyayalaya finds the`
  line `adjournment of the hearing beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be recorded in`
  line writing.
  line
  line `(8) The Gram Nyayalaya shall dispose of the application made under sub-section (1) within a period`
  line `of six months from the date of its institution.`
  line
  line `(9) The judgment in every suit, claim or dispute shall be pronounced in open court by the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya immediately after conclusion of hearing or at any subsequent time, not exceeding fifteen days,`
  line `of which notice shall be given to the parties.`
  line
  line `(10) The judgment shall contain a concise statement of the case, the point for determination, the`
  line `decision thereon and the reasons for such decision.`
  line
  line `(11) A copy of the judgment shall be delivered free of cost to both the parties within three days from`
  line `the date of pronouncement of the judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (9589)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Execution of decrees and orders or Gram Nyayalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9589&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) the judgment passed by a Gram Nyayalaya`
  line `shall be deemed to be a decree and it shall be executed by a Gram Nyayalaya as a decree of the civil court`
  line `and for this purpose, the Gram Nyayalaya shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Nyayalaya shall not be bound by the procedure in respect of execution of a decree as`
  line `provided in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and it shall be guided by the principles of`
  line `natural justice.`
  line
  line `(3) A decree may be executed either by the Gram Nyayalaya which passed it or by the other Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya to which it is sent for execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (9590)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Duty of Gram Nyayalaya to make efforts for conciliation and settlement of civil disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9590&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every suit or proceeding, endeavour shall be made by the Gram Nyayalaya in the first instance,`
  line `where it is possible to do so, consistent with the nature and circumstances of the case, to assist, persuade`
  line `and conciliate the parties in arriving at a settlement in respect of the subject matter of the suit, claim or dispute and for this purpose, a Gram Nyayalaya shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed by the`
  line `High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in any suit or proceeding, it appears to the Gram Nyayalaya at any stage that there is a`
  line `reasonable possibility of a settlement between the parties, the Gram Nyayalaya may adjourn the`
  line `proceeding for such period as it thinks fit to enable them to make attempts to effect such a settlement.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any proceeding is adjourned under sub-section (2), the Gram Nyayalaya may, in its`
  line `discretion, refer the matter to one or more Conciliators for effecting a settlement between the parties.`
  line
  line `(4) The power conferred by sub-section (2) shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other`
  line `power of the Gram Nyayalaya to adjourn the proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (9591)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Appointment of Conciliators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9591&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of section 26, the District Court shall, in`
  line `consultation with the District Magistrate, prepare a panel consisting of the names of social workers at the`
  line `village level having integrity for appointment as Conciliators who possess such qualifications and`
  line `experience as may be prescribed by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting fee and other allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions for`
  line `engagement of, Conciliators shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (9592)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Transfer of civil disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9592&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The District Court having jurisdiction may, on an application made`
  line `by any party or when there is considerable pendency of cases in one Gram Nyayalaya or whenever it`
  line `considers necessary in the interests of justice, transfer any case pending before a Gram Nyayalaya to any`
  line `other Gram Nyayalaya within its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (9593)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Proceedings to be in the official language of the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9593&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The proceedings before the Gram`
  line `Nyayalaya and its judgment shall, as far as practicable, be in one of the official languages of the State`
  line `other than the English language.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (9594)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Application of Indian Evidence Act, 1872.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9594&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `A Gram Nyayalaya may receive as evidence any`
  line `report, statement, document, information or matter that may, in its opinion, assist it to deal effectually`
  line `with a dispute, whether or not the same would be otherwise relevant or admissible under the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (9595)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Record of oral evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9595&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `In suits or proceedings before a Gram Nyayalaya, it shall not be`
  line `necessary to record the evidence of witnesses at length, but the Nyayadhikari, as the examination of each`
  line `witness proceeds, shall, record or cause to be recorded, a memorandum of substance of what the witness`
  line `deposes, and such memorandum shall be signed by the witness and the Nyayadhikari and it shall form`
  line `part of the record.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (9596)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Evidence of formal character on affidavit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9596&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The evidence of any person where such`
  line `evidence is of a formal character, may be given by affidavit and may, subject to all just exceptions, be`
  line `read in evidence in any suit or proceeding before a Gram Nyayalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Nyayalaya may, if it thinks fit, and shall, on the application of any of the parties to the`
  line `suit or proceeding, summon and examine any such person as to the facts contained in his affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (9597)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Appeal in criminal cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9597&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law, no appeal shall lie from any judgment, sentence or order of`
  line `a Gram Nyayalaya except as provided hereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie where—`
  line
  line `(a) an accused person has pleaded guilty and has been convicted on such plea;`
  line
  line `(b) the Gram Nyayalaya has passed only a sentence of fine not exceeding one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to sub-section (2), an appeal shall lie from any other judgment, sentence or order of a`
  line `Gram Nyayalaya to the Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `judgment, sentence or order of a Gram Nyayalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court of Session may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(5) An appeal preferred under sub-section (3) shall be heard and disposed of by the Court of Session`
  line `within six months from the date of filing of such appeal.`
  line
  line `(6) The Court of Session may, pending disposal of the appeal, direct the suspension of the sentence or`
  line `order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(7) The decision of the Court of Session under sub-section (5) shall be final and no appeal or revision`
  line `shall lie from the decision of the Court of Session:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall preclude any person from availing of the judicial`
  line `remedies available under articles 32 and 226 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (9598)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Appeal in civil cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9598&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908) or any other law, and subject to sub-section (2), an appeal shall lie from every judgment`
  line `or order, not being an interlocutory order, of a Gram Nyayalaya to the District Court.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie from any judgment or order passed by the Gram Nyayalaya—`
  line
  line `(a) with the consent of the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) where the amount or value of the subject matter of a suit, claim or dispute does not exceed`
  line `rupees one thousand;`
  line
  line `(c) except on a question of law, where the amount or value of the subject matter of such suit,`
  line `claim or dispute does not exceed rupees five thousand.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the judgment or order of a Gram Nyayalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that the District Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) An appeal preferred under sub-section (1) shall be heard and disposed of by the District Court`
  line `within six months from the date of filing of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(5) The District Court may, pending disposal of the appeal, stay execution of the judgment or order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line
  line `(6) The decision of the District Court under sub-section (4) shall be final and no appeal or revision`
  line `shall lie from the decision of the District Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall preclude any person from availing of the judicial`
  line `remedies available under articles 32 and 226 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (9599)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Assistance of police to Gram Nyayalayas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9599&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every police officer functioning within the`
  line `local limits of jurisdiction of a Gram Nyayalaya shall be bound to assist the Gram Nyayalaya in the`
  line `exercise of its lawful authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Gram Nyayalaya, in the discharge of its functions, directs a revenue officer or`
  line `police officer or Government servant to provide assistance to the Gram Nyayalaya, he shall be bound to`
  line `provide such assistance.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (9600)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Nyayadhikaris and employees, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9600&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Nyayadhikaris and the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Gram Nyayalayas shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act`
  line `in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (9601)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Inspection of Gram Nyayalayas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9601&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may authorise any judicial officer superior`
  line `in rank to the Nyayadhikari to inspect the Gram Nyayalayas within his jurisdiction once in every six`
  line `months or such other period as the High Court may prescribe and issue such instructions, as he considers`
  line `necessary and submit a report to the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (9602)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9602&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three years from`
  line `the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (9603)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of High Court to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9603&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the form and dimensions of the seal of the Gram Nyayalaya under section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the form, the manner and the fee for institution of suit, claim or proceeding under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(c) manner of service on opposite party under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(d) procedure for conciliation under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(e) qualifications and experience of Conciliators under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(f) the period for inspection of Gram Nyayalayas under section 37.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued by the High Court shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (9604)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778&sectionId=9604&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00009_200904_1517807319778
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Gram Nyayalayas under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(b) the sitting fee and other allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions for`
  line `engagement of, Conciliators under sub-section (2) of section 27.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
